-- Stage subscriptions with dedup and null handling

        status,

    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1

-- int_subscriptions_enriched.sql
```sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with user and plan details
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        sub.subscription_id,
        sub.user_id,
        sub.plan_id,
        sub.started_at,
        sub.ended_at,
        sub.status,
        usr.company_id,
        COALESCE(pln.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(cmp.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} sub
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} usr
        ON usr.user_id = sub.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} pln
        ON pln.plan_id = sub.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} cmp
        ON cmp.company_id = usr.company_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    company_id,
    tier,
    industry
FROM source
```

-- fct_monthly_subscriptions.sql
```sql
-- Calculate monthly subscription metrics
WITH billing_source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('month', bil.event_month)::DATE AS month,
    sub.tier,
    sub.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT sub.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(bil.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT sub.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM billing_source bil
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_enriched') }} sub
    ON sub.subscription_id = bil.subscription_id
GROUP BY
    DATE_TRUNC('month', bil.event_month)::DATE,
    sub.tier,
    sub.industry
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier ASC,
    industry ASC
